perform multi-anchor joint conditioning\n388:3. Methodology: AnchorWeave\n399:trajectory using a coverage-driven, 3D-aware retrieval strat-\n400:egy (Sec. 3.3) and rendered as anchor videos. These anchor\n402:Multi-anchor Weaving Controller, which jointly reasons\n403:over multiple anchors via shared attention and pose-guided\n409:3.1. Preliminary: Video Diffusion Models\n480:AnchorWeave: World-Consistent Video Generation with Retrieved Local Spatial Memories\n522:coverage is empty. Retrieval terminates when the uncovered region is 0%, the retrieval budgetK is exhausted, or the remaining memory\n523:pool is empty. For clarity, coverage is computed with a single frame here, while in practice is aggregated over multiple frames per chunk.\n526:generation, and extra camera intrinsics and anchor videos\n534:3.2. Local Geometric Memory Construction\n552:3.3. Coverage-driven Memory Retrieval\n562:late memory retrieval as avisibility coverage maximization\n564:imize coverage along the target camera trajectory within\n570:ory that provides the largest new coverage of the currently\n630:AnchorWeave: World-Consistent Video Generation with Retrieved Local Spatial Memories\n665:Multi-anchor\n669:Fused anchor\n680:anchor video 1\n687:anchor video K\n698:Figure 3.Architecture of multi-anchor weaving controller. Anchors are encoded and jointly processed by a shared attention block,\n700:retrieved-to-target camera poses for the 1 to K anchor videos, where each denotes the relative pose between the camera associated with a\n708:retrieved memory, we render anchor views along the target\n709:camera trajectory within the chunk, producing anchor clips\n711:we pad the remaining anchor slots with fully-invisible an-\n712:chor clips to keep a fixed number ofKanchors per chunk.\n713:For the rendered anchors, we compute the retrieved-to-target\n718:then concatenated across chunks, resulting in K anchor\n720:target pose trajectories. These anchor videos and their pose\n722:3.4. Generation with